doc.previous: The median income for a household in the county was $35,966, and the median income for a family was $40,260. Males had a median income of $30,120 versus $24,686 for females. The per capita income for the county was $18,497. About 14.5% of families and 18.0% of the population were below the poverty line, including 22.9% of those under age 18 and 18.9% of those age 65 or over.
after: As of 2011, 51.2% of Miami-Dade residents were foreign born (including naturalized American citizens.)[26] In 2010, Cuban exiled refugees made up the largest population of immigrants (with more than half of the population,) with Nicaraguans coming in second, Haitians in third, Colombians followed by in fourth place, then Hondurans, Dominicans, Venezuelans, Peruvians, Jamaicans, Mexicans, Argentinians and Salvadorans amongst the highest group of expatriates.[27]
